# KibblRx Privacy Policy
 
**Effective Date:** March 18, 2026
 
## Overview
 
KibblRx is a pet medication tracking app developed by Twelve52. Your privacy matters to us. This policy explains how KibblRx handles your data.
 
## Data You Enter
 
All data you enter into KibblRx — including pet profiles, medications, dose history, and symptom logs — is stored locally on your device and, if you have iCloud enabled, in your private iCloud account.
 
iCloud syncing is managed entirely by Apple through CloudKit. Your data is stored in your personal iCloud container, encrypted by Apple, and is not accessible to Twelve52 or any third party. If iCloud is disabled, your data remains on-device only.
 
Twelve52 does not collect, transmit, or store any of your pet or health data on external servers. We have no access to the information you enter into the app.
 
## Advertising
 
KibblRx displays banner advertisements to users on the free tier of the app. These ads are served by Google AdMob, a third-party advertising service provided by Google LLC.
 
When ads are displayed, Google AdMob may collect and use certain data for the purpose of serving and measuring advertisements, including:
 
- Device identifiers (such as the Identifier for Advertisers, or IDFA, if you grant permission)
- IP address
- General device information (device model, operating system version)
- Ad interaction data (impressions, taps)
 
This data is collected and processed by Google in accordance with Google's Privacy Policy (https://policies.google.com/privacy). Twelve52 does not have direct access to the personal data collected by Google AdMob.
 
**Opting out of personalized ads:** When you first open KibblRx, you will be asked whether to allow the app to track your activity across other companies' apps and websites. If you choose "Ask App Not to Track" or disable tracking in your device settings (Settings > Privacy & Security > Tracking), Google AdMob will serve non-personalized ads and will not use your IDFA.
 
**Removing ads entirely:** Subscribing to any KibblRx+ plan (monthly, yearly, or lifetime) permanently removes all advertisements from the app. No advertising data is collected while a subscription is active.
 
## Data We Do Not Collect
 
Twelve52 does not operate servers, databases, or analytics platforms. Beyond the advertising data collected by Google AdMob as described above, we do not collect:
 
- Names, email addresses, or contact information
- Pet names, medication details, or health records
- Location data
- Usage analytics or behavioral data
 
## Third-Party Services
 
KibblRx integrates with the following third-party services:
 
- **Apple StoreKit** — for processing in-app purchases and subscriptions, governed by Apple's Privacy Policy (https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/)
- **Apple CloudKit** — for syncing your data across your own devices via your iCloud account, governed by Apple's Privacy Policy
- **Google AdMob** — for serving advertisements to free-tier users, governed by Google's Privacy Policy (https://policies.google.com/privacy)
 
## Data Retention
 
Twelve52 does not retain any of your data. Your app data exists only on your devices and in your iCloud account. Deleting the app removes all local data. Removing KibblRx data from iCloud can be done through your device's iCloud storage settings.
 
Advertising data collected by Google AdMob is retained and managed by Google in accordance with their data retention policies.
 
## Children's Privacy
 
KibblRx does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. The app contains no user accounts and no social features. Advertisements displayed to free-tier users are served by Google AdMob, which does not serve personalized ads to users identified as children.
 
## Changes to This Policy
 
If we update this privacy policy, we will post the revised version at this URL with an updated effective date. Continued use of KibblRx after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
 
